analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. The FAS will be used for all efficacy and baseline analyses.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. The FAS will be used for all efficacy and baseline analyses.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >= 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Per Protocol Analysis Set represents a subset of the FAS and consists of all FAS subjects who did not meet any major protocol deviations during Period 1 of the study.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Per Protocol Analysis Set represents a subset of the FAS and consists of all FAS subjects who did not meet any major protocol deviations during Period 1 of the study.
analysisPopulations.criteria: FAS AND no major protocol deviations during Period 1

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. For the Safety Analysis Set, subjects are assigned to a treatment group based on the 'as treated' treatment group, regardless of the treatment randomized.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. For the Safety Analysis Set, subjects are assigned to a treatment group based on the 'as treated' treatment group, regardless of the treatment randomized.
